4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a municipality with at least
6 25,000 inhabitants may extend its corporate limits by
7 resolution of the municipality's governing body and
8 special election.
9 This bill would authorize any municipality to
10 extend its corporate limits by resolution of the
11 municipality's governing body and special election.
12
13
14 A BILL
15 TO BE ENTITLED
16 AN ACT
17
18 Relating to annexation; to amend Section 11-42-40, Code
19 of Alabama 1975, to further provide for annexation by
20 resolution of a municipal governing body.
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
22 Section 1. Section 11-42-40, Code of Alabama 1975, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24 "§11-42-40
25 Any city having 25,000 inhabitants or more, as shown by
26 the last federal census, from time to time, may extend its
27 corporate limits in the manner and with the rights, powers,
28 and privileges as set forth in this article, but the
